PROTON TOTAL REACTION CROSS SECTIONS AT 28.5(1.5) MEV.

x4codes.hlp: Atomic Energy Research Establishment (AERE), Harwell, United Kingdom

x4freetext: ISOTOPICALLY PURE ELEMENTS CA-40,FE-56,CO-59,NI-58,
NI-60,SN-120 AND PB-208 WERE USED.

x4codes.hlp: Rutherford Appleton Laboratory, Chilton, England, United Kingdom

x4freetext: /BY AUTHORS/.THE UNCORRECTED CROSS SECTIONS (SIGMA-R)
ARE DIRECTLY RELATED TO THE MEASURED ATTENUATIONS A BY
THE EXPRESSION A=N*SIGMA-R,WHERE N IS THE NUMBER OF
NUCLEI PER CM**2 OF TARGET AND WAS DETERMINED BY
WEIGHING TO AN ERROR OF 0.5%.EACH VALUE OF SIGMA-R
IS THE AVERAGE OF RESULTS FROM SOME 10 TO 20 INDIVIDUAL
RUNS.THE STANDARD DEVIATION QUOTED ON THIS AVERAGE IS
DERIVED FROM THE OBSERVED SPREAD OF EXPERIMENTAL
RESULTS,AND IS IN EACH CASE CONSISTENT WITH THAT
ANTICIPATED FROM THE TOTAL NUMBER OF COUNTER.
/BY AUTHORS/.TWO CORRECTIONS MUST BE APPLIED TO THE
VALUE OF SIGMA-R IN ORDER TO OBTAIN THE TRUE TOTAL
REACTION CROSS SECTION.THE FIRST OF THESE,FOR INELASTIC
PROCESSES LEADING TO AN ENERGY LOSS OF LESS THAN 6 MEV.
THE ORDER CORRECTION INVOLVES SUBTRACTION OF THE CROSS
SECTION FOR ELASTIC SCATTERING OF PROTONS OUTSIDE OF
THE SOLID ANGLE SUBTENDED BY THE STOPPING DETECTOR.
.PROTON STOPPING DETECTOR.
NEEDED CORRECTIONS ON ELASTIC AND INELASTIC SCATTERING
ARE INCLUDED.
